The terms of the board members shall be as follows:
The initial board members shall be appointed as determined by the Governor for the following terms:
Two (2) behavior analysts shall serve for one (1) year;
Two (2) behavior analysts shall serve for three (3) years;
A psychologist shall serve for two (2) years;
One (1) parent shall serve for one (1) year; and
One (1) parent shall serve for two (2) years;
The terms of subsequent board members shall be for three (3) years; and
A vacancy of any board member shall be filled in the manner of the original appointment for the unexpired portion of the term only or as provided by KRS 12.070. The Governor, after notice and opportunity for a hearing, may remove any member of the board for malfeasance, neglect of duty, incompetency, or revocation or suspension of a license.
